'''Sugawara Shrine''' (すがわらじんじゃ) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Kokurakita-ku|ja|小倉北区}}, {{ill|Kitakyushu|ja|北九州市}}, [[Fukuoka Prefecture]], Japan. It is one of the many shrines dedicated to {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真}}, a deity associated with learning and scholarship.

== Origin ==
{{section-stub}}

== Annual Events ==
* [[January 1]]: New Year’s Day Festival (歳旦祭)
* [[April 24]]–[[April 25|25]]: Spring Festival (春季大祭)
* [[July 25]]: Summer Purification Festival (夏越祭)

== Access ==
* The shrine is accessible via the {{ill|Kitakyushu Monorail|ja|北九州高速鉄道}} at {{ill|Tanga Station|ja|旦過駅}}.

== External Links ==
* {{Official website|name=Sugawara Shrine}}

